title: Hilton Daytona Beach Oceanfront Resort
text: So incredibly disappointed.. I use to love the Hilton Daytona oceanfront property but this stay was definitely disappointing. The young lady who checked us in for our stay was very pleasant and as a Hilton honors member they upgraded our room from ocean view to ocean front. After arriving in the room I went to use the restroom and noticed the bathroom hadn’t been cleaned. During these times with many uncertainties this was very concerning. I searched our room after noticing the bathroom wasn’t clean and found a bug shell on our bed! We called the front and the quickly moved us to a different room . No bug shells on this bed but the room was still very sad and the pictures on the wall even had broken glass in the frame. I talked so highly of this property and after this stay I am embarrassed of how highly I spoke of it . I also paid $20 for self parking and when I mentioned the gate was up and not closing they said valet was working on it only to wake up this am and it still be open .

title: Harrah's Cherokee Valley River
text:
This place is "Starting" to grow on me. Much better atmosphere than my visit back in November 2021. Masks are encouraged but not Forced on you. The Food court has gotten back into it's groove and the options are plentiful and given a 4 Day 3 night stay we had tried just about everything with no complaints. The main Restaurant was superb, my Steak couldn't have been cooked any better and exactly as I requested. Medium with no seasoning only salt and hint of cracked pepper. This place still has plenty of real table games(it's nice have a real human for a dealer). They still have a mix of virtual table machines but the balance was much better than a lot of other out of the way casino resorts are going. Great selection of slots but still like all the other casinos, they are very tight. The areas for those not able to gamble was open and they had plenty to do to keep them busy. I recommend you check out their website to see all the options and entrainment available to anyone traveling with young people. I seen quite a few on this trip and they seemed quite happy and talkative. In all, we enjoyed this visit but I still miss my Wisconsin favorites. However, this one will definitely grow on you. Enjoy and definitely Good Luck! You'll need it, Lol.
Update 8-14-22; I just spent two nights here and this place just keeps getting better. Slots seem to be a little less tight and I actually walked out ahead this time, significantly 😁. I noticed a lot more staff, slot attendants doing hand pays, Security, cleaning personal and the drink servers we're around checking up on everyone very regularly. I still have to get used to the higher drink prices ("We're not in Wisconsin anymore"😂). The area is Beautiful and lots to do if you need a break and you're not in the gambling mood. If only they had a Spa this would definitely be a 5 ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ Resort. Hint, hint!!!
name: Kenton Wiedenbeck

title: Quest Motel

title: Hilton Daytona Beach Oceanfront Resort
text: Absolutely and positively phenomenal. This was an honestly once in a lifetime experience that my partner and I will cherish until the day we die. The friendly staff, the luxurious room with a private butler, the positively magical food, and all of the experiences they help organize and facilitate. Words cannot describe how amazing this hotel is. I haven’t stopped talking about it since we got back. We are a month removed and it still feels like a dream. I hope to work and save enough so that I can one day attend the event which was my absolute highlight of the entire trip. If you’re reading reviews for this hotel for private reasons of whether or not to attend I think you know the answer, but if you want something that feels classy and historic but at the same time more welcoming that your living room like other more classically styled fine hotels, I couldn’t imagine staying anywhere else. text: Lovely hostel experience! Check in was simple and accommodating. Clean and tidy room. Great outdoor sitting space out back. If you get there early enough, they have parking available- which I definitely recommend splurging to get if you bring a car. To park on the street, I noticed you needed to have a permit. The breakfast in the morning was simple yet good too
name: Morghan Townsend

title: Historic Route 66 Motel
text: Comfy beads, warm room, clean towels, and great customer service.
name: Sonia Duenas

title: Quality Inn & Suites
text: I can't say enough good things about this place! Staff is so awesome! So peaceful and quiet. The most comfortable bed EVER!
name: Stacey Walton

title: Marriott St. Louis West
text:
Severely Customer Service from the valet, started at the door we walked into hotel and walked at the desk for 2 mintues as 2 employes stood around conversations. Waited for some one to help us with a smile on our faces but the person was too busy chewing gum and chatting with an employe in front of us.
Went to Pub and sat in a booth with our families ordered a drink and they mixed it in half a pint glass that was made out of cardboard, it was not the normal glass the drinks were served in.
I asked the bartende if they had pint glass in the kitchen that was made out of glasses, not cardboard and saved the bagged pint glass so we can show the manager after we got out bags out of Bagagre.
The first hotel on our 50th aniversary 👩‍🎓✈️
Never will take this long Waited 2 hours for our bags to be put in our cars.
name: Peter Wright

title: Marriott St. Louis West
text: Hotel room was very dirty upon arrival. There were hairs all over the floor, leftover trash from the previous guests and toothpaste on one of our "clean" towels. Staff was friendly, but the hotel itself was dirty.
name: Cassie Shurtz

title: Ray’s Splash Planet
text: Kids enjoyed the pool..Too hot in the pool area, lockers have no keys or way to secure belongings they really need to expand
name: Vergiekitten Weatherspoon

title: Wyndham Garden Cross Lanes Charleston
text: Great food, great Italian food and old Italian bread you can't get anywhere else plus pastas and other dishes that are some of the best Italian food that I have ever had, I highly recommend this restaurant
name: Nicola Burgess

title: Hinkle Fun Center
text: We bring the family here on a regular basis. The putt putt is a lot of fun. Some times they have discounted games, two for one. Generally busy, but not so busy we have to wait for others to finish putting. Two courses to choose from (lakes or rivers). Discount for putting both. Free parking and entrance. Lots of ticket giving games provide opportunities to trade tickets for prizes, but this is not the reason we go. My kids have been invited here for birthday events that provide pizza, games, putt putt, gocarts, and bumperboats. If your interested they also have a laser tag play area and paintball course.
name: Teil Plont

title: Saltgrass Steak House
text: T-bone steak cooked to perfection. Nice staff and atmosphere.
name: Karl-Christian Huldgaard Christensen

title: Quality Inn & Suites
text:
If I could give negative stars, I would.  The room itself was a little sketchy with something growing on the wall, the ceiling was pealing in the corner and was breaking away along the exterior wall. The tub had serious rust stains, and the phone didn't work. That's relevant because I needed to call the front desk when I woke up and found that my car had been broken into.

I had to call on my phone and the front desk just asked what room I was in. They didn't even apologize that this crime had been committed, didn't offer to send someone to clean up the glass, call the cops, anything. And when I checked out they didn't say anything. I received more sympathy from the cops (just filed a report, they didn't send anyone out) and the glass repair company Safelite. They apologized that this had happened and helped me find a repair location that can get me in tomorrow in a different state. Quality Inn isn't quality at all. They don't care about your stay at all.
name: Rebecca Larsen

title: Hampton Inn & Suites Orange Beach/Gulf Front
text:
This is one of the best hotels that I have ever visited...everything about it was 5 star!
I will be returning with my husband for two nights for our 5 year wedding anniversary celebration. I can't wait 😍😍😍😍
name: Lynne Connolly

title: Days Inn & Suites by Wyndham Kansas City South
text: Spent a night to see the factory. Hotel is close to the factory district. Room made for four people, soitfeels bigger than it is. Opting for the self-parking. 5 dollars. There are 2 parking areas one building away. I parked across from a 711, portside shopping and ten restaurants and a Starbucks! That started out as a joke, buti laughed for an hour and a half about it.
name: Dennis Holloway

title: PUMP Restaurant Lounge
text:
Came for dinner on Saturday evening.

HOSTS - we came to check in for our reservation at 4:57, we were told that our 5pm table was not ready yet and were asked to wait by the bar. After 10 minutes of no one coming to get us, we went back and asked to be seated.

DRINKS - we got the pink Vanderpump sangria and dirty cowboy, both were good.

FOOD - ordered the Tuna tartare, which was good, but extremely oily. The appetizer came out really fast. For main course we got the Mykonos salad and the Salmon salad, both were average. Brussels sprouts in the Salmon salad tasted burned and unseasoned.

FINAL THOUGHTS - the waiter has asked me to clarify my order three times which was kinda frustrating. I also don’t understand why we couldn’t be seated when we were early to a reservation that the restaurant was extremely empty. When I moved my chair back I bumped into the table behind me which also had a party seated there.

I came for the hype, but I will not be dining here again.
name: Shani Levi

title: The Edge Paintball Experience
text: PMX truly has everything a paintball player could want except a pro shop and equipment rental. The field layout is incredible and varied enough to be fun over several visits with easy access to extra equipment and guns, plenty of parking, and an easy entry.
name: Duncan Wood

title: Bridges Bay Resort
text: Nice rooms, we had a suite for a wedding event.  Will do again for sure!!  Full kitchen, stove, full fridge, dishwasher etc.  Plates, glasses, silverware etc.  The presidential suite at the Kalahari in the Dells doesn't have a full kitcken!!!  Two decks. Pull out sofa.  Rooms 1245-1247 are on the far corner of the 2nd floor over looking the Waterfront.  Arcade, full indoor pool and waterslide park.  We missed the outdoor one but it was still great!  A few minor misses on the rooms & services...no morning continental breakfast.   Bathroom showers need to be re-grouted, deep cleaned.  2nd floor hallway carpet had a few carpet bubbles you can easily trip on if you're not careful.  Overall...a really nice stay.  Will book again.
name: Ryan Tostenson

title: Golden Green Hotel Daily & Extended Stay - Loving Hut Vegan Restaurant
text: Old building needs refurbishing, but even the better room we got showed a lack of pride in the workmanship.
name: Rhonda-Elaine Bonney

title: First Western Inn Caseyville
text: Comfortable bed, great pillows, electric fireplace.  No breakfast, but the little refrigerator has bottled water for purchase.  The front desk is friendly and helpful. One little problem is that I saw house cats lurking about.  They were both friendly and cute, but I blame the motel management for not keeping the cats on leashes.  I hope that management reads this and does something about it.
name: Kerry Atkinson

title: Frank's of Parkville
text: Happy eating!
name: Brandon Owen

title: Sky Zone Trampoline Park
text: My son loves Shadowland especially the bounce balls!
name: Pauline George

title: Addis Restaurant
text: It was my first time. This place is absolutely amazing. They are very friendly and the food is amazing. I bought 4 specials to go. I had never seen a place with this variety. Their deserts looked just as amazing as the savory dishes. I wish we had a place here like this.
name: Rachael Wall

title: J. Alexander's Restaurant (Overland Park Grill)
text:
My wife and I ate here for our annual New Year's Eve dinner. It wasn't the first time we've eaten aJ. Alexander's either. Just like every other time, they brought their A-game. The salad are all mixed and tossed, steaks were cooked perfectly, their Mac & Cheese is heavenly and the side of broccoli was perfectly cooked through but still had a little crunch to the stalk. My hat's off to the kitchen staff!
Every time we have visited, the wait staff is friendly, attentive and very knowledgeable about the menu. They always seem to know exactly when to stop at the table for a drink refresher or the next course of the meal without making you wait to long or hovering. Also, unlike most other restaurants we have visited on NYE they didn’t give us a set amount of time before running is out. Instead, they let us sit at our table and enjoy our date night together.
Oh, I highly recommend the deviled eggs with camels bacon if it's on the menu when you go too.
name: Franken Bunny

title: Historic Route 66 Motel
text: Great motel. Would recommend. Friendly staff. Checked in late but there is someone all night at the reception. The place is really cool. You also get a 10% discount in roadkill cafe if staying here
name: Ivanna Ricci

title: Jaegers Subsurface Paintball
text: Great local field! Just went for our first time and will definitely be a regular customer. Super friendly staff, and my kids had an absolute blast. Highly recommend.
name: Conor Payne

title: Historic Route 66 Motel
text: This place was incredible!!! The rooms were clean and updated.  We had the Harley Davidson room and it was amazing!!! The woman that checked us in was so friendly and nice! Made us feel so welcome!  I would stay here again in a heartbeat!!! You will not be disappointed in this amazing motel right on historic Route 66
name: Alicia

title: Cinemark 20 and XD
text:
The theater produced a great picture and amazing sound.
Ready to go back!
name: Shannon Webster

title: Arabia Steamboat Museum
text: I had found out about the rediscovery years ago and it had been on my bucket list for a while. It was a lot more to look at than first expected. I could probably come back and stay hours again.
name: Mike Swisher

title: Paulo and Bill Restaurant
text: We really enjoyed our first experience here! Their menu isn't as big as some of our other favorites, and they didn't provide complimentary bread with our meal, but the food was great and our server was very attentive and friendly!
name: John F

title: Marhaba Grill
text: Very certain! Friendly environment:) Great variety, and ver, very tasty !!! Must try!!!
name: T K

title: Days Inn & Suites by Wyndham Kansas City South
text: Not good at all. Staff all nice yes but the condition of the hotel overall not ok. The cleanliness was poor. Some rooms are unfinished. Some smell like urine. Very drafty during the winter. Breakfast was trash. And there are bed bugs and bettles present in some areas and rooms this was the BIGGEST DISGUST AND TURN OFF. I do not have bugs of any type in my home and NEVER have much less in my bed so with that being said I will not sell myself short in someone else's establishment that's meant to make others feel comfortable.  I was un easy the remainder of my stay and had to do alot of mental conditioning to get past what i seen even after switching rooms... I'm a super visual person and once i see something its difficult to un see. I will not be back and wish like hell I could atleast get half of my money back for the major inconvenience. For this to not have been discovered tells me someone is not doing their job or fair share here. Thanks but no thanks Days Inn. When I visit it's for weeks to a month at a time so I take my booking seriously for the safety and comfort of my family above all else. This was unacceptable. And it was kinda just brushed over as if this was a normal complaint. SMH
name: Chocolat- e

title: SEA LIFE Kansas City
text: Well-organized. Unique experience with history and pictures. No hidden costs/ fees. I would have preferred a little more space to walk around so I didn’t have to keep holding my bag while walking & more time to enjoy and take pictures in the house. I liked that it was a small group of visitors (about 20) and the owner/ docent took the time to get to know our names. I quickly interacted with each exhibit.
name: Valerie Rose

title: Wyndham Garden Cross Lanes Charleston
text: The building is being updated by the new owners. The hotel will be very nice when complete. The new breakfast area is almost complete, but, for now, they served breakfast in their on-site grill. The indoor pool is gorgeous, but the hot tub is still  under construction.  I  would be happy to return in a year when everything should be done.
name: Louisa Halmi

title: Trap Music Museum
text: I went here the day after they opened up and the museum is beautiful. Their space is so nicely set up, lit, organized and has a gorgeous gift shop. I actually got to watch the glaze making AND paint a Raku tile. There's also a cafe. I would 100% go again. If you like ceramics, art and pretty things I highly recommend this trip. ___ I partially went to this to paint but it ended up being a fun trip to go on alone. I had a great experience here, the art studio is cute and inviting. There's a coat and bag check which is nice and helpful. The barista at the cafe is great, the studios are happy, the gift shop is wonderful and I pretty much just had a great time. The prices for our time are 15 for a adult for a single and 25 for a couple. Totally worth it. You'll have a great time. They accept most credit cards too.
name: Naomi Mitchell

title: Vallarta's Mexican Restaurant
text: One of the tastiest and freshest places I've found in KC. The salsa is great and everything is discounted if you pay with cash. Treat yourself.
name: Iain West

title: Smiley's Golf Complex
text: Super fun...a lot harder than expected! Added goes for safety first on the golf course! And a nice setting for a nice hot day! Highly recommend it! We will be back for more 😊👍🏼
name: Megan Davison

title: Quality Inn & Suites
text: Close to the Bluff park and mall. About 20 mins. from the coast. Rooms clean. Staff courteous and helpful. Hotel restaurants had great food.
name: Sylvia Davis

title: Saltgrass Steak House
text: Very consistent and the food has a great flavor. It's moderately priced but the steak is much better than the Roadhouse. Definitely recommend.
name: Anar Gadirli

title: J. Alexander's Restaurant (Overland Park Grill)
text:
J. Alexander's Restaurant in Missouri is a true gastronomic haven, offering an unparalleled dining experience that leaves guests longing for more. The elegant, warm atmosphere is complemented by the exceptional service, making you feel welcome from the moment you step through the door.

The menu boasts a diverse array of exquisite dishes, masterfully crafted by a team of culinary experts. A standout feature of J. Alexander's is their commitment to top-notch presentation, ensuring every plate is a visual masterpiece. Pair your meal with their extensive wine selection or indulge in one of their decadent, house-made desserts for the ultimate finale to your dining experience.

J. Alexander's Restaurant in Missouri is a must-visit destination for food connoisseurs and casual diners alike. It is the epitome of fine dining, blending culinary artistry with exceptional hospitality to create an unforgettable experience. Don't miss out on this hidden gem in the heart of Missouri!
name: Steven Sierra Alcabes

title: Round 1
text: My 8 year old daughter and I had so much fun at this place! Comparing to other places like Dave and Busters, they are a lot less. We got 4 tokens, made a card and it was 4$ total including the tax. We both had such a great time, I cannot wait to go back!
name: Stephen Wallis

title: Hinkle Fun Center
text: What a fun place to play and make your money disappear in a matter of minutes. It is a great place to bring kids. Tons of activities inside to do. It's clean and the staff is super cool. The prices are pricey but it is in line with its competition.
name: Stanley Rose

title: Round 1
text: Kids had a great time. They stayed all day on a Tuesday.
name: Julie Ford

title: Best Western Colorado River Inn
text: May 1st check in time 4Pm and in 3mins it was done.... Checkout time 11am and in 5 mns it was done... Had a Quiet room in the first floor and it was nice🤗🤗🤗 Staff was great and polite no rush no pressure.🤗
name: Frederick Hale

title: Best of the Wurst German Kitchen
text: I truly enjoyed every bite of my meal! I'm also a big fan of the speilia coffee as well! My waitress was very nice and I had no complaints whatsoever! Lucky one is definitely one of my go-to restaurants! I highly recommend crème brûlée and pretzel bread... it's ah-mazing.
name: Olivia Smith

title: El Sombrero Mexican Restaurant
text: The "Hat" serves some of this city's best salsa.
name: scott “Simpleman”

title: Marriott St. Louis West
text: This hotel is SO NICE. They deadass have an espresso machine with almond milk & syrups. Their breakfast is luxury level delicious. The rooms are clean and have good views. The staff here is very friendly and keep to themselves but are very helpful when needed. The bar is great and all of the bartenders that served me were super kind and great conversationalists. Coming from someone who was in the service industry for 2.5 years their kitchen and their bar space is very clean and organized. Would definitely stay here again, it feels like home.
name: Payten Vincent

title: Breakout KC Escape Room | River Market
text: The employees were amazing and really nice.  They really go out of their way to make sure that you have fun and enjoy the game. The games were very challenging and exciting.  I had more fun than I could have imagined.
name: Emily Williams

title: Marhaba Grill
text: Great place to eat at.  Very nice place.  I had the Vegetarian sub, vegetarian shawarma pita, and a small tea.  Everything tasted good!  The waitress was so nice to me and was helpful.  They also have air condition!
name: Jane Taylor

title: Hampton Inn & Suites Orange Beach/Gulf Front
text: We made an overnight trip to this little gem! So original and clean. They have a coin operated laundry. If staying more than one day pack light and they have the dry cleaning service. I wish more hotels in AM have this amenity. Inexpensive  restaurant tight bar indoor pool. I would highly recommend staying here!
name: Lorraine Lynch

title: Plate Restaurant - Leawood
text: Really good service and food that feels like it's home cooked italian.
name: Mitchell Reed

title: Trap Music Museum
text:
Mostly my kids and I enjoyed this museum which is split into 5 different floors. First, the dinosaur exhibit is all about the evolution of dinosaurs from Earth, the other dimension and nearly ending the planet. All in all, a very entertaining exhibit for young minds that all.

Second, there are models of different kinds of dinosaurs and all their evolution stages.

Third, there are dioramas and a video explaining the history of the World Park Zoo.

Fourth, I enjoyed the display on the culture of New Guinea and the instruments whereas the kids enjoyed the tikis of Hawaii.

Now, my kids and I are not attracted to bugs. With that said, there is an entire exhibit that is dedicated to interesting bugs and has plenty of interactive things for kids to do. It is a very cool exhibit with its colorful exhibits and interactive things to learn in small details.

All in all, I would say it is a must see while in the Cape Cod area
name: Jonathan Warner

title: Hinkle Fun Center
text: My favorite is... go cart, laser tag and bumper car! So much fun for team building :) cannot miss
name: Xiaohan Wang

title: RODEO MEXICAN RESTAURANT
text: Someone please explain this to me. You get 3 crispy tacos meal for $9.79. You get 2 soft tacos meal for $9.79. But if you buy the tacos individually they are $2.80 each no matter if you get crispy or soft. Why with the meal, do you get 1 less soft taco? Look at the menu and see what I mean.  I brought this up to the manager and they told me it’s because it’s a meal. They obviously don’t get what I was asking.
name: Michelle Sexton

title: The LINE LA
text:
I love boutique hotels. And The Line LA is now on the top of my list. The design is super fun, while being both thoughtful and playful. 5 stars for the service, the staff here is friendly and engaged. I’m on the 8th floor in a King room with an expansive view of the Hollywood hills. My room has the bed, a desk and additional seating which I really enjoy using. I like how spacious my room is. I don’t want to get out of bed, it’s cozy and comfy, not stiff. The bath did not disappoint, soft towels and a dojo type robe that I appreciated for its light weight.
I had dinner and wine at the hotel, and again, great service. The food had a fresh take that was interesting and delicious. I’m in town for the weekend and The Line is a perfect fit.

This is an update. I returned to The Line for three days during Christmas. Same great service. My family joined me for Christmas Day brunch at the newly opened Openaire restaurant. The meal featured rolling carts with sides that were inventive, tasty and fun.
name: Deborah Kuchar

title: Best of the Wurst German Kitchen
text:
The food is pretty good.  Not great, but good.  We did the Wurst platter, some perigees and spaetzel.   All good, with a special nod to the kielbasa which was fantastic.

The place is well worn, and the marina isn't ever going to be confused for Monte Carlo.

The staff were friendly.

The biggest thing....it's on the water....which is really nice.  If the place were in Maine or Mass it would be "rustic".  BYOB...OK food and a nice setting....it's worth a visit.  The place has Octoberfest written all over it.  Cool weather on the deck with a few beers and a brat or two....I'll be back.
name: R G

title: Vallarta's Mexican Restaurant
text: We had a great experience here! The service was fast and friendly. The food was great and the portion sizes were right. We will be back again.
name: William Cochrane

title: The Edge Paintball Experience
text: Good field! Just hated all the pesky  Mosquitoes.
name: TheCorgiMilitia Taskforce132d

title: Home grown GA Restaurant
text: We loved this place, my family and I. As soon as we walked in it felt like home. The manager was super friendly, the waitress was quick and hilarious. The food was good, it certainly didn't have the best burgers, but I liked it. The patio seating is the way to be! My husband wants to go back and can't stop saying what a great time he had!
name: Lewis Williams

title: Quality Inn & Suites
text: This place is amazing well decorated and nice amenities they even have an indoor pool
name: Paul Bishop

title: Honeycomb Bed & Breakfast
text: I truly enjoyed the hospitality!
name: Kieran Tucker

title: Holiday Inn Express & Suites Swift Current, an IHG Hotel
text:
Hotel is beautiful from the outside but age catching up with it on the inside.

Great facilities, decent breakfast, lovely and helpful staff.

Bathroom is not so spacious and beds are somewhat comfortable.
name: Abimfoluwa Olaleye

title: Trap Music Museum
text: ITS LITERALLY THE BEST MUSEUM I'VE EVER BEEN TO EVER...
name: FRANK ROSS

title: Breakout KC Escape Room | River Market
text: Love this place very fun experience with friends to try and figure out individual puzzles & find the items with other people.  Not as easy as it sounds and you don't have much time! Will be returning when I can!
name: Alison Lee

title: Free Play Arcade - Richardson
text: This is a great location to bring the whole family. A lot of people have tried this concept but Free Play did it right. All the games work very well and they have a great mix of the classics. The beer selection was surprisingly decent but the prices were a little high. This is a place you can definitely spend more than 2 hours at. During the weekends that can get crowded with a ton of kids. I will be going back soon.
name: Adam Floodman

title: Harrah's Cherokee Valley River
text: Great hotel and i can't praise the staff enough. They are the best. I loved the hot tub and pool . Lovely rooms . Especially room 407 .
name: Barry Pope

title: Round 1
text:
1/2022:  RECOMMEND, but 3.5 stars if possible due to 2 details:

If possible, go during the WEEKDAY for Unlimited bowl until 5pm for $11.99. I've hurt my arms & shoulders from bowling way too many games during this inexpensive time and improved my bowling scores.  (Thank you Round 1).

I've enjoyed going to Round 1 to relax and enjoy the oversized Pac-man game and bowl some stress away.  I have not tried the food nor drinks there because I just go in to play games.

Mostly clean, spacious and social distancing  protocols are  in effect.  Team members were constantly cleaning.  My only negative comment is that no one has cleaned the escalator entrance and it looks unwelcoming/unsightly.

Overall, give Round 1 a try and see what you think about it.  Enjoy the games!
name: Demetris

title: Free Play Arcade - Richardson
text: Great classic video games, beer, wines & drinks. They even have a small menu. Cool to see classic Asteroids & Space Invaders as well as other classics. Tablet alcohol purchases make it very convenient to end the day too.
name: Laura Martin

title: RODEO MEXICAN RESTAURANT
text: Always so friendly and good food endicores
name: Melissa Walker

title: Kura Revolving Sushi Bar
text:
Every once an a while it's nice to take a stroll over to the erie canal and millcreek. Tonight we found it to be cold and windy, but the people watching and restaurants were just as upbeat and enjoyable as the other nights. Most notably another one of our favorite sushi bars/restaurants, quality sushi & meats together.

We do not chip any cards but instead pay cash, we enjoyed 2 orders of sushi, 5 bowls of ramen, miso soup, egg roll, veggies and we were able to split everything w 6 different people. We also were able to buy some take home gifts for all our employees who have been working hard for about 3 weeks straight.
Few notables for us;
-cooked the egg all the way
-the regular sushi is fresh! The nigiri combo packs are all delicious. The yellowtail was our favorite and the only one with special points. One of our favorites $8.95

-the
name: Victor Williams

title: Hungry Howie's Pizza
text: Awsome food and nice variety.  I think they cater and event's.
name: Frances Butcher

title: Best of the Wurst German Kitchen
text: Great food
name: Eleanor Gibbons

title: Smiley's Golf Complex
text: Absolutely love the course!  My dad and I tried it today for the first time and we will be back for sure.  We played immediately after rain and the course was in great shape, hardly soggy anywhere.  We even saw a blue heron on hole #9.  Also, love that there isn't a bunch of tall grass in the rough.  Greens were in great shape too and a decent challenge putting.  Lastly, the staff was very nice/welcoming.  I accidentally booked two tee times through Golf Now and the gave me a rain check to make up for my mistake!  What service!  All around a 5 out of 5 experience, thank you!
name: Donkey Kong

title: Quest Motel
text: My daughter and I were on a journey from Nebraska to Denver and ended up getting stranded here. We found a room here for the night, the manager brought us a heavy military blanket for the bed and we left in the morning with the battery on the car fully charged. I really liked the ghost hunt tools in the lobby, haha.
name: Frank Wilkinson

title: Breakout KC Escape Room | River Market
text: Really fun puzzles and our room "The Hero" was just a blast. Not to mention the very funny, friendly, and overall lovely staff! Val was a great game guide by balancing small hints and allowing us to fumble our way to solving it. We made it with 3 seconds to spare! Our group will definitely come again to do another room. :)
name: Elio Fraenig

title: Hilton Daytona Beach Oceanfront Resort
text:
Very out dated, no amenities,mediocre service. Way overpriced.
MY SUGGESTION TO HILTON IS SELL THIS SO CALLED RESORT PROPERTY TO MOTEL 6,AT LEAST THEY WILL KEEP THE LIGHTS ON FOR YOU.
my second and final stay (gold member)
name: Sohile Shaheen

title: Addis Restaurant
text: Absolutely superb doro wat!!!  I rarely had this good Ethiopian food even traveling 2 months in Ethiopia!
name: Pius Lee

title: Arabia Steamboat Museum
text:
I absolutely loved their Egyptian section - the sarcophagus there was massive and so ornate- they have a replica with a person in there to give you an idea of the scale 😕

Very excited to check out their future exhibits- they have lots of great items! Endocrinology got added to the museum since I was there 😊
name: Emma Davidson

title: Frank's of Parkville
text: Nice little cozy Italian restaurant! Very friendly staff and great food!
name: Nitish Chaudhari

title: Paulo and Bill Restaurant
text: Quiet intimate atmosphere.  Great service.
name: Jordan Clements

title: Chicago Getaway Hostel
text: My boyfriend and I stayed at the Chicago Getaway over the winter for three nights. We loved it! It was clean, affordable, and the walk to the train wasn't too far. It feels just like staying at a hotel. I will definitely stay here again next time I visit!
name: Samantha deManbey

title: The Westin Hilton Head Island Resort & Spa
text: What an awesome experience we had over Independence Day weekend! The pool is fantastic, with plenty of room for kids and adults to play, not too deep, a spacious jacuzzi nearby, and plenty of lounge chairs (although here's a tip: claim your chairs by 8am on busy weekends!). We enjoyed the games and activities for the 4th of July, and the BBQ buffet (with s'mores) was delicious! The private beach access is a huge bonus as well. We look forward to returning for another family getaway!
name: Chris Schweighart

title: Saltgrass Steak House
text:
Ordered a Pittsburgh medium, it had the perfect amount of char just the way I like it...also you can taste a bit of smokey flavor which I really love.
The kitchen was working in full speed and you can tell they got it together on a busy sunday night!
fast efficient ob.
Will come back again
name: Stanley Parkin

title: Quest Motel
text: Clean, comfy and roomy but still cost effective.   Very friendly, caring and helpful owners.   Next time im going through Sask ill definitely be sure to stay here.
name: Jonathan Devries

title: Wyndham Garden Cross Lanes Charleston
text:
This hotel is luxury quality with access. It's Oasis.
Maid rooms are cleaned daily, product is top of the line, the service desk checks and responfs to requests promptly and apologetically. The breakfast had the breakfast of your choice and all dishes of the making up, there is a separate area for the kids, adjustable height tables and chairs, two types of toast (the bread is really really good and poached eggs) scrumptious bacon and sausage and just potato sticks to your liking. Buffet has travel yogurt, muesli and juice as well as extra options like a pancake machine and a bodka machine directly behind it. The Pool slides and 8 lane wide lap pool. 24 hr gym and outdoor track. Coffee, sausage pancake and eggs, the availability of an Apple computer for printing at all hours, the Stamps and Kindles, the refrigerators and microwaves are an added bonus. We think it's worth the price and will come
name: Zoe Begum

title: Courtyard by Marriott Charlotte Matthews
text: Nice rooms. Too many kids, oof
name: Brenda Evans

title: Hinkle Fun Center
text: My kids had the best time at Jumpy Time for Kid’s Birthday Party. Staff Is great. Thank you so much.
name: Bethany Johnson

title: Plate Restaurant - Leawood
text: Wonderful people and pizza, and full bar! And the pizza is a lot bigger than what you pay for!! Very good pepperoni and cheese pizza!! Will come again!! Thank you Sposato for making my family happy every time we bring them here!!
name: Jay Finch

title: J. Alexander's Restaurant (Overland Park Grill)
text: I tried this place again at the request of a friend. Unlike my first visit I was pleasantly surprised. The host was really nice, energetic and entertaining to our group. The entrées were served hot and fairly quick given the size of our group. Main course was good. For desert, the Powerhouse Pie was wonderful, filling, and shareable (recommended). So many different flavors on one fork. The chocolate cake was one of the most moist full flavored chocolate cakes I have tasted. I will be back as this place has turned a corner from my visit a couple years ago.
name: Earl Fowler

title: Home grown GA Restaurant
text: Great food worth the wait
name: Justin T Brown

title: Smiley's Golf Complex
text: Great customer service. Great price. Danny and steve are extremely nice to all their customers. They've been in game with the Louisville community for 50 years. They get it...they have amazing customer service and the 60 minutes of go-karting for $20is definitely worth it. It's a really popular place. Great for date night!
name: Elliot Baker

title: Paulo and Bill Restaurant
text: Very good value. I had the spaghetti special, and came with salad, garlic bread, and ice cream. Family friendly place!
name: Gordon O'Sullivan

title: Smiley's Golf Complex
text: Great mini golf place! I suggest y’all give it a try!
name: Craig Riley

title: J. Alexander's Restaurant (Overland Park Grill)
text: Of course they have fabulous food but what I really noticed was super fast and high quality service!! An extra unexpected treat was the fabulous decorative hedge on the front patio! Absolutely one of a kind!!  Love this place!!
name: Joyce Birch

title: Denver Zoo
text:
The Zoo of lights is pretty amazing!!!
It's very magical being under all the lights
The glasses that come with the glow package are pretty cool as well
Dress warm if you go 🙂
name: Mel

title: Hilton Sandestin Beach Golf Resort & Spa
text: I chose a room with only sea view while making reservation.  At the hotel, they gave me a room with a side view and a pool view, and the balcony door lock of the room was problematic.  Then we went and asked for a different room.  but we paid too much for this room.  It was cheaper when I made the reservation, they took more money for the night.  To the 2nd room.  When I walked into this room it smelled of marijuana.  Then we went to room 3 again.  hotel rooms were not clean.  Those who made reservations were not good. If we choose another room.  They said they will get more money.  This was not my fault. It was not the right of his money.  I don't plan to go again.
name: Sergey

title: Honeycomb Bed & Breakfast
text: The BEST!!
name: Danielle Jones

title: The Westin Hilton Head Island Resort & Spa
text:
The Westin is suppose to be a premium brand for the big money you’re paying. The beach is public and people with tents and loud music are allowed to use the beach property. We paid for lounge chairs and umbrellas and some quiet time. But did not get it. The hotel
should have a private quiet section for their guests with no tents, loud music. July is a busy time here. If you’re looking for quietness maybe stay here in the spring or fall.
name: J Sa

title: Plate Restaurant - Leawood
text: Reasonably good food, not incredible, but nothing to really complain about. A bit pricey for lunch portions. Decent service, friendly staff.
name: Emily Vainer

title: Electric Playhouse
text: Great spot to take your children everyday or to friends parties or just make it a date night 😍
name: Roy Edwards

title: SEA LIFE Kansas City
text: Would recommend for younger kids, maybe elementary school aged. Took my teen there, and although she did have fun because she loves marine animals in general, this place is geared more for the younger ones. And look for “less than busier” times if you like to read everything. There is lots of great information all over. Have fun!
name: Pauline Torres

title: Cinemark 20 and XD
text: I never understand why people bitch about cheap people eating and drinking inside the theatre. The whole reason they have a concession stand is to sell popcorn and other snacks like candy, sandwiches, candy, etc. If you have to go to the bathroom go at the beginning of the movie and try to go fast and make it in under 10 minutes but hopefully the movie isn't as good as this movie.
name: Toby Harding

title: El Sombrero Mexican Restaurant
text: Rolled tortas and chicken nachos.
name: Diana Hammond

title: Bowlero Cherry Creek
text:
Friendly staff.  Great music.  TV projectors are fun for sports games. League pricing is just $2.35/game and free shoes. Plus 2 free games a week.  If you arent in one it can be expensive. Leagues are the way to go.
The lanes are oiled once to twice a day. Bathrooms clean.  Floors are clean.   Ball damage is low and if it happens they will fix it or replace it at no cost.
Also TenBack pro shop has one of the best coaches in the state Shawn Lee. Ball, bag, and shoes cost only $129
name: gammafilter

title: Bridges Bay Resort
text: Great food, great service
name: Christopher a Stickler

title: Chicago Getaway Hostel
text: I've been traveling for three years, save four months in two years, and this was my favorite hostel yet. I was the sole guest for two nights and thoroughly enjoyed the solitude and the shade being provided by the trees. It feels well kept, the staff was mostly friendly, and I met some new fellow backpackers here. Additionally, if you like dogs as much as I do you're in luck. They have a big icky cat that made off with half a burger from the hostel porch.
name: Henry Coates

title: Best Western Colorado River Inn
text:
Casino is OK, on off days no deal at all and on busier days it was fun.

The suites are very nice, live in deals for rooms not for free, the living room is not designed for watching tv. so if you made the tiny living room you will hate this room. It is NOT a sofa Suite.

FOOD is even casino food bad, Blue Marlin or LaGoona is the best food on this Great Bend area.

Red Robin and Chipotle are other places that are closer.

The hotel would be great for Hollywood movie possibilities such as if you want to recreate an "A Street Warrior" movie set. It is no deal for your money unless under the beer deal... probably stay away from that deal too.

BAD ATM is at the casino!!
name: Oliver Davies

title: The LINE LA
text:
Very clean, rooms are a good size and they have a wonderful breakfast! Immaculate room! No bugs or debris. Bed was very comfy. Breakfast was amazing. They have coffee and a variety of dishes & drinks. The parking lot is very small and we had trouble fitting into ours. There are TV channels but just local ones (Portland) and they are in black and white and low resolution. But the free Wi-Fi is awesome!
Great location! Right on the river! Nice staff was welcoming and helpful! I'd stay here again!
name: Frederick Carroll

title: Trap Music Museum
text: Great place, everybody should go there ones. Very friendly people.
name: Robert Loeffler

title: Hungry Howie's Pizza
text:
You'll get a slice or two of pizza and an education on the draft and canned beer selections. Most importantly you'll leave with a fat and happy warming belly. I love that they bake the calzones fresh while you wait. My pics are actually of two slices of pepperoni pizza, ricotta cheese glazed wings, and a calzone loaded with broccoli, spinach, and mozzarella. I wasn't planning on sharing however my friend was having a rough week and I wanted to cheer her up. We each ate half before I even finished my beer😎. Life could be so much easier if we'd reign in our compulsion to hoard food.

Every little bit count when ordering from Kickback's.
name: Sian Campbell

title: Saltgrass Steak House
text:
This is a fantastic little hidden gem near Rt 6 surrounded by trees and off the beaten path. It's easy to miss as there is no clear signage just one sign in front of the building you are looking for.
More of an order at the counter type establishment seating only 30. There was an older couple ahead of us that were taking their good old time quite awhile.


They don't accept plastic, so make sure to bring cash. They have several items cooked over the open fire from a list of daily specials and sandwiches.
We ordered the filet with a loaded baked potato for $27.00. They come with soup or salad which is first come first served  since if you have to overly staffed.
We were brought sliced hot peppers in olive oil to snack on while we waited.
The salad was great, I stayed with the low fat ranch house dressing and the fresh salad greens were fresh tasting...not wilted like other restaurants.
Just a great value
name: Lynn Lynch

title: Chicago Getaway Hostel
text: The cleanest hostel I’ve ever been to. Great variety of different rooms private and communal. The breakfast was decent (like any hotel) but the kitchen is amazing. A great place to stay regardless if you’re on a budget or not. When I come back I will rebook at this hostel!
name: Rye Ledford

title: Frank's of Parkville
text: Very tasty food and great service!
name: Terence Roberts

title: The Edge Paintball Experience
text: Amazing staff. No matter what age you are, the staff and people there make sure you're welcome and included. $15 to play for 8 hours, I love it. don't waste you're money on a single 20 minute game of Lazer tag.
name: Alex Laws

title: Hilton Sandestin Beach Golf Resort & Spa
text: We are currently holding "duel hotel citizenship " between here and the neighboring Luau Condos next door. My in-laws and children are staying here so husband and I are back and forth.  We love the Sandestin Hilton for all the convenience of the restaurants and beach access.  You must have a wrist band to use these facilities,  and when my Mother in law explained the situation,  guest services was happy to accommodate us with wrist bands and parking until we could check into our condo later in the day.  Be sure to check out Barefoot Grill by the pool for burgers,  fries,  chicken tenders and more.  Piknix is a great place for ice cream and Starbucks is inside near the large indoor pool. There is a raw sushi bar inside and a really nice steakhouse in which you will want to dress up for.  Towels for the use of the three pools and three hot tubs are provided.  The view from their room is really nice.  Overall,  very impressed!
name: Stephanie Honeycutt

title: Jaegers Subsurface Paintball
text: Great place to shoot.  Will be back.
name: Sharon Gilbert

title: Hinkle Fun Center
text: My son had a blast!! Great place
name: Hayley Thomas

title: J. Alexander's Restaurant (Overland Park Grill)
text: Great service, very friendly and helpful. Food was ok and over priced.
name: Victoria Lewis

title: Honeycomb Bed & Breakfast
text: Comfy beds! Great little breakfast, and the lady who took care of us was so helpful and friendly, and let us use the laundry. Great location, too, right downtown and LITERALLY a 30 second walk to the delicious "Chicken Shack" restaurant. Highly recommended!!
name: Brenda Hudson

title: Arabia Steamboat Museum
text: Any words I type here cannot do this place justice.  The largest collection of antebellum artifacts in the world.    It's like an 1850's Wal-Mart.  A true family endeavor.  You cannot believe how amazing this place is.  Do yourself a favor and check it out.   You wont be disappointed.
name: Tim Piland

title: Marine Motel
text: Super clean was very excited that they have charges that run the heat and the ac.Very affordable not to once will I stayed in a hotel end up paying more ✌🏻 than this room
name: Geoffrey Burns

title: Lalibela Ethiopian Restaurant
text:
First Ethiopian experience was a plus! We did the vegetarian entree sampler for 3. Was nice to try 8/9 vegetarian entree options they had! From what I could tell, the injera was super fresh and good bread/utensil!
Flavors were very diverse! Fresh veggies and they were all pretty “al dente”. Love that they were firm and not overly soggy like a lot of veggies in stews like that can be. Service was slightly slow but completely acceptable and worth it! Just plan to spend some time here.
name: Trenda Martin

title: Honeycomb Bed & Breakfast
text: Place is nice, clean and well-maintained. Cindy is a caring host and knows how to run a business very well!! She makes a tasty, artistic breakfast, too! :) stayed there couple of nights, twice in 2015 and 2017.
name: Rami F.F

title: SEA LIFE Kansas City
text: It seems like it has improved from 6 years ago... sea dragon exhibit was awesome, the whole family loved it!
name: Donkey Kong

title: Wyndham Garden Cross Lanes Charleston
text: Friendly staff and nice rooms.
name: Lydia Sanders

title: Hotel Bel-Air
text: Concord have been to it once before and I have to say that it is rich in history. It is now fixed with a Great staff and terrific dining experience especially in the lounge area. Warm with clean and rich in atmosphere.
name: David Richardson

title: Frankie's of Charlotte
text: It was so much fun. The kids had a blast and my wife and I had fun to.
name: Jade Clark

title: Quality Inn & Suites
text: The room smelled like mold, there were cigarette holes in the blankets, the doors were dirty, the room itself was absolutely gross, noticed some bed bugs, and the front desk customer service was terrible. They kept trying for cash instead of a card, seemed reluctant to refund the room cost, though it was returned as well as the unmentioned $100 deposit. Card was charged twice for $70. Lots of people hanging around outside. Didn't feel comfortable leaving my car unattended even just for the 5 minutes we were in the room. Pretty sure the 5* reviews are fake. DO NOT STAY HERE. Go to the Comfort Inn a couple of miles away.
name: Kayla Crowe

title: Wendy's
text: I been in many fast food places. But none beats the juicy tasty triple burger freshly made and their hot potatoes with chili. Hey! Dont need to believe it. Just come down and jump on this triple burger. 👍
name: Juan Reyes

title: Ray’s Splash Planet
text: great place, clean facility and a lot of fun!
name: Henry Clements

title: Best Western Colorado River Inn
text: The most DISGUSTING place I've ever had to stay! It wasn't clean AT ALL. Hand prints on the mirror, mold and pee all over the toilet. The bath was so disgusting, I put a towel down to shower. Front desk was rude, as well. $200/night! He acted like I couldn't pay it... Like that hotel was celebrity status of something. It was so awful.
name: Nichole House

title: The LINE LA
text: ZERO HOT WATER in the showers today!
name: Josh Kim

title: Kura Revolving Sushi Bar
text:
This place is really really really really good!!

Paid $10 for 1 dozen and they gave me 2 extra jumbo rolls 

Yummy yummy!

Dedicate to york
name: Brian Ward

title: Paulo and Bill Restaurant
text: THIS IS A GREAT PLACE FOOD WAS WONDERFUL 🤤...
name: Hugh McCleary Jr

title: SEA LIFE Kansas City
text: My granddaughter wanted us to go with her and our great grandson to the Aquarium. It was a very nice place and he enjoyed it so much.
name: Nancy Betz

title: SEA LIFE Kansas City
text: My kids and I love this place. We love learning about the sea creatures and how we can help them
name: Micheala Crowder

title: SEA LIFE Kansas City
text:
Always a fun time and easy to spend almost an hour here even in the middle of winter weather.
Visited for the first time, had grandkids with us, wished we had visited years ago.
It was great having them run free, no burdens or concerns just having fun.
Visiting this place in the warmer seasons would definitely focus on the coaster side though.
We will definitely be making several returns in the coming months.
Thanks Frontier.
name: Gareth Heath

title: Crowne Plaza Shenandoah - Woodlands Area, an IHG Hotel
text: Nice hotel. Room was large and clean. Breakfast was poor with very little options. Hotel gym was nice. A lot of free parking around the hotel. It is easy to arrive by car from the airport (about 30 min drive). Fast check in and check out.
name: Idan Ra

title: Days Inn & Suites by Wyndham Kansas City South
text: Awesome little place, the modern retro theme was very cute and cool. The arcade was fun... the bar had a nice vibe and the bartenders were great. I love that there's a free to use pool upstairs. The rooms are clean and spacious... room service was fast and friendly. Rooms were well stocked with a microwave, mini fridge and Keurig. The shower is a nice veranda with lots of space. And the bed was super comfy! Will definitely stay here again.
name: Leslie Taylor

title: Ray’s Splash Planet
text: Great place to take your kids!!! Small price BIG FUN!
name: Just Smith

title: Denver Zoo
text: Great Zoo. It is kept up nice and many of the animals seemed well taken care of 👍. Also it is a lot larger than I had been expecting and we were well worn out by the end of the day. REally nice place to take your kids or grandkids so they get to see some nice things.
name: Charlie Bailey

title: Quest Motel
text: I was a bit leary as I drove in and saw the outside of the motel, but I was in for a nice surprise.  The rooms were nice and well kept.  The bed was very comfortable with soft sheets and blankets.  The pillows were so nice and fluffy.  There was a roomy refrigerator, small microwave, and coffee maker.  I would definitely stay there again.
name: Carrie

title: Best of the Wurst German Kitchen
text: Really great food!!!
name: paul wiedemann

title: PUMP Restaurant Lounge
text: We enjoyed the gorgeous atmosphere and nice cocktails.  It was a lot larger than I was expecting.  Even though it was crowded we had great service!  If I lived in the area I think this would be somewhere I would frequent
name: kendra komp

title: Marriott St. Louis West
text: When we got to our room there was dried urine on our toilet seat. It took 4 calls and an hour and half for someone to come and take care of it. I was disappointed! It was after 11pm before they sent someone, and we were tired from travel.
name: Susan Johnson

title: Best of the Wurst German Kitchen
text: A diamond in the rough! Delicious German food creek side. They have many different things to order, but I am especially looking forward to schnitzel night which is on Wednesday.
name: Jennifer Wolfenden

title: Arabia Steamboat Museum
text: I love history and amazing stories and facts to go with it. This is a must see for anyone visiting Kc, I'm lucky enough to live here and didn't realize I should of come sooner to this attraction. I was blown away by the entire thing from the determination of the ppl that found it to the background as to how the midwest was founded. Amazing how much effort is put into this amazing exhibit! I will be continuing to see this place as time goes on because they grow the artifacts as they uncover from preservation. Go see it you won't be disappointed!
name: SHag

title: Bridges Bay Resort
text: Please bring your own snowshoes or rent, a lot of trails are closed but there are 4 open trails, you can rent sleds at 1/2 mile south of the park on the west side of the road.
name: Georgia Barlow

title: The LINE LA
text: Openaire was delicious. The wagyu sirloin steak, ahi poke, pig ears, and the fish were all delicious. If I had to pick one winner, it would be the pig ears appetizer. But everything was delicious along with the atmosphere  and decor. Will be back for sure.
name: Lazenca

title: Trap Music Museum
text: If u don't know what a trap house looks like on the inside and would like to know how they started this is the place to visit. It was fun.
name: James Mobley

title: Courtyard by Marriott Kansas City at Briarcliff
text: I worked the garage door opener and got locked in, 2 free #2 meals there, walk the 3 blocks to Safeway first to find a small cooler, and the next morning got a free breakfast. Reasonably priced, excellent staff. Would definitely do it again. It would be hnnaic as they were swamped.
name: Jane Khan

title: Marriott St. Louis West
text: Overall, this was a nice place to stay. Rooms were clean and the staff was very accommodating. Hotel is kinda in an office park so you need to drive   to get to anything more fun. Our room had a nice view.
name: Clint F

title: Harrah's Cherokee Valley River
text: Nice place to stop on our vacation in the Smoky Mountains
name: Daniel Ficke

title: Bridges Bay Resort
text: Was here for a hiking trip. The staff in the store was very friendly. Got a nice little map of all the places around the area to hike. Stores food and cook supplies, little or anything you might need. There's a hiking guide in the room to help you get a good hike in.
name: Francesca Jones

title: Cinemark 20 and XD
text: Had my kids with me and they just enjoyed the hot chocolate. When they were not sipping, they were making smiles watching movies. This is a "must do". We saw "Dumbo", two hours was a great time!
name: Jodie Johnson

title: Chicago Getaway Hostel
text: Really nice place!  I’ve never been to a hostel before so I went in expecting a dorm as I was under the impression (wrongfully so) that this is what a hostel is.  I had a room with a bed and a TV for about 15 USD closer to the weekend.  I booked this place for a concert and I stayed here for 4 nights and essentially it was a hotel for the cost of a hostel.
name: Geoffrey Edwards

title: Jaegers Subsurface Paintball
text: Nice new paintball field, clean, not crowded and  a lot of targets. Getting the airsofts and GA guns to work the paintguns was not easy to do at first, but then became so easy we stopped concentrating and we were out of air. Treats owner, if you see him and want to go back for whatever reason, tell him and he gives you a second round for free or 20% off or whatever and it's not split with anyone else. Definitely worth the drive.
name: Grace Nash

title: Kura Revolving Sushi Bar
text: Great experience both ordering and pick up!  The quality of food is great and fresh.  Will definitely continue ordering from direct order when I'm on the go!
name: Lee Ford

title: Courtyard by Marriott Kansas City at Briarcliff
text: Absolutely beautiful view
name: Julie Hebert

title: Best of the Wurst German Kitchen
text: Absolutely Phenomenal Cuisine, Amazing People, Wonderful Atmosphere & Breathtaking Views.
name: Melissa Bouvier

title: J. Alexander's Restaurant (Overland Park Grill)
text: This is a very nice restaurant. It has all home style food and desserts. You can’t get a fresher piece of pie anywhere else. The service is excellent and very friendly. I highly recommend you visit this restaurant this winter.
name: Julie Elliott

title: Ray’s Splash Planet
text: Great park for the family. Loved the caves, a little dark but totally worth it. The zip line was a hit between my kids and myself. The only thing missing is a bigger wave pool but not big enough to comeback over it. Still it’s a fun, clean, family park. UPDATE: I received an amicable response to my re charge my complaints above.  Perhaps the ride operators were overtaxed  or some other poor management. That said, I was so impressed and happy to charge re point out that my positive experience last night and the on point response i received makes them a five star park and I regret having kicked it down to a three star. Thanks, See you soon and bring a towel!
name: Katie Patel

title: Golden Green Hotel Daily & Extended Stay - Loving Hut Vegan Restaurant
text: Had to move out of the first room due to stains everywhere, including the sheets and the bathroom. Second room was acceptable but still not comfortable. The temperature control was confusing and ineffective, involving an unmarked switch next to the thermostat. Check in staff ignored the reservation and only checked us in for 1 day, then tried to charge late fees to stay the rest of the days we'd reserved, AND demanded we check out then check back in to get a different room. Also, the elevator doors open well before you reach your floor, which is scary. And one of the adjacent rooms had clearly been battered down by police and had a bullet hole in it. Decided that literally anywhere else would be an improvement.
name: Ray Black III

title: Hotel Bel-Air
text: They have old fashion pool and fun for even 50 years old adults
name: Bryan Sullivan

title: Quality Inn & Suites
text: Non smoking room smelled strong of  cigarette smoke. Was so strong that the t- shirt I slept in reaked of it when I pulled it out of my suitcase today to wash it. Carpet was absolutely disgusting,bottom of my socks were black. Toilet was so loose it slammed into the wall if you sat on it. Toilet seat was nasty.Very thin walls,can clearly hear everything in your neighbors room.Room doors slam close. Very dirty and run down
name: melissa cole

title: Arabia Steamboat Museum
text: Absolutely worth the visit. A great way to share natural science with kids of all ages. Well organized, informative, and fun. Look for the night sky planetarium shows, they are my favorite but hard to get tickets for since they sell out quickly. Great for exploring independent or as a group. Each section tells different information about its topic.
name: Joel Jones

title: Addis Restaurant
text: Tasty food and nice place
name: Leslie Cartwright

title: Smiley's Golf Complex
text: Dog-friendly, reasonably priced, and well maintained!  Ice cream and candy selection is even cute.  Can’t say enough good things, still a kid at heart, even in my 30s.
name: Michelle Wilson

title: Frankie's of Charlotte
text: Great place with lots of activities. Plenty of space. We enjoyed.
name: Kerry Brennan

title: Marriott St. Louis West
text: This 5 star resort has it all! Outstanding food, rooms, staff and off-site activities. It’s a 5 star offering every time you are here, whether it goes out at the park or just visiting the spa. Kudos to my favorite hotel in the area!
name: Jayne Higgins

title: Courtyard by Marriott Kansas City at Briarcliff
text: our second time here... same great experience... hospitality and welcome is warm, friendly and exceptional!! right off the interstate, pet friendly, clean and updated. we will be back again...
name: Leah Norris

title: Harrah's Cherokee Valley River
text: Run down.  Lost reservation. Unscheduled reservation rate charge. Please make sure paypal is safe and is expected. There are still lights on at this hotel. RUN RUN RUN.
name: Christopher Allen

title: Cinemark 20 and XD
text:
It's well
I like it also good for family and kids
name: Nicholas Summers

title: Hungry Howie's Pizza
text: Trust the process 😉
name: J. Jones

title: First Western Inn Caseyville
text:
I like this place better than the Motel 6 and Quality Inn.

They have RV parking... :)
name: Joe Bender

title: Paulo and Bill Restaurant
text: The food was tastefully prepared, fresh and scrumptious. Staff presented each dish very professionally and elegantly.
name: Linda Spencer

title: Home grown GA Restaurant
text: The "Bay Point Burger" was GREAT! Large, toasted bun. Everything was fresh, tasty and exactly what we expected. We sat in a booth, the staff was very courteous and friendly. Enjoyed the salad bar VERY much. Very impressed with the variety, cleanliness, and diversity as well.
name: Karen Jones

title: Addis Restaurant
text: Food and hospitality are great! The steak sub is beyond amazing! Coffee is good too.
name: Michelle Midlick

title: The Westin Hilton Head Island Resort & Spa
text: Our 2nd time here, great hotel, decent food for a casino. Could not rate the Galaxy Restaurant poorly because we went when the remodel was going on, due to our enjoyment of the other places we went we will rate this favorably. Comfortable clean rooms, friendly staff, nice pool area and nice workout machines in fitness center.
name: Margaret James

title: Arabia Steamboat Museum
text:
Very cool exhibit on several Native American cultures.
Worth the visit to have a greater appreciation of Native WOrlds. I would definitely recommend a visit.
name: Arthur Sutton

title: Sky Zone Trampoline Park
text: My little girl totally enjoyed her birthday party! The host Was adorable and did an amazing job.Was in and out in a couple of hours with no clean up! Was great! Would definitely recommend!
name: Vanessa Soto

title: Holiday Inn Express & Suites Swift Current, an IHG Hotel
text: Very horrible tonight, wife and I waited forever in lobby for ten dollars worth of quarters for the slot machines, with it being the 2nd and 3rd time stopped over the years, nothing has changed, maybe it is time we look elsewhere.
name: Molly Gilbert
